<p class="mb-4"><strong>Important:</strong> &quot;Specialty coffee&quot; officially requires 80+ SCA points. Below that, it&#39;s technically not speciality.</p>
<hr class="my-8 border-black/20">
<h2 class="font-typewriter text-2xl md:text-3xl mb-4 mt-12">Direct Comparison</h2>
<div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8"><table class="w-full font-mono text-sm">
<thead class="border-b-2 border-black">
<tr>
<th class="text-left py-3 pr-4">Aspect</th>
<th class="text-left py-3 pr-4">Commercial Coffee</th>
<th class="text-left py-3 pr-4">Speciality Coffee</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20"><strong>Origin</strong></td>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20">Unknown, blend</td>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20">Traceable to farm</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20"><strong>Species</strong></td>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20">Robusta + arabica</td>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20">100% arabica</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20"><strong>SCA Score</strong></td>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20">&lt;80 or unscored</td>
<td class="py-3 pr-4 border-b border-black/20">80+ (up to 90+)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
